{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id798626a9-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s1547"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1547"},"text":"§ 1547.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Rules and regulations; employees","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"In the performance of his functions and duties under the provisions of sections 1544 to 1548 of this title, the Secretary of Commerce is authorized—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id798626aa-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s1547/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" To prescribe, amend, and repeal such rules and regulations as he may deem necessary, and to accept contributions for carrying out the purposes of said sections; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id798626ab-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s1547/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" To employ, subject to chapter 51 and subchapter III of chapter 53 of title 5, one special assistant and not to exceed five artists and illustrators.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id798626ac-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1940-07-19/ch642/s4"},"text":"July 19, 1940, ch. 642, § 4","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/54/774"},"text":"54 Stat. 774","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1949-10-28/ch782"},"text":"Oct. 28, 1949, ch. 782","children":[],"tail":", title XI, § 1106(a), "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/63/972"},"text":"63 Stat. 972","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/93/193/s2"},"text":"Pub. L. 93–193, § 2","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1973-12-19"},"text":"Dec. 19, 1973","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/87/765"},"text":"87 Stat. 765","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id798626ad-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id798626ae-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"id798626af-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section was formerly classified to ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t16/s18c"},"text":"section 18c of Title 16","children":[],"tail":", Conservation."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Provisions of par. (b) authorizing the Secretary of the Interior to employ “without regard to the civil-service laws” were omitted as such employment is subject to the civil service laws unless specifically excepted by those laws or by laws enacted subsequent to Executive Order 8743, ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1941-04-23"},"text":"Apr. 23, 1941","children":[],"tail":", issued by the President pursuant to the "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1940-11-26/ch919/tI/s1"},"text":"Act of Nov. 26, 1940, ch. 919, title I, § 1","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/54/1211"},"text":"54 Stat. 1211","children":[],"tail":", which covered most excepted positions into the classified (competitive) civil service. The Order is set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s3301"},"text":"section 3301 of Title 5","children":[],"tail":", Government Organization and Employees."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“Chapter 51 and subchapter III of chapter 53 of title 5” substituted in par. (b) for “the Classification Act of 1949, as amended” on authority of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/89/554/s7/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 89–554, § 7(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1966-09-06"},"text":"Sept. 6, 1966","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/80/631"},"text":"80 Stat. 631","children":[],"tail":", the first section of which enacted Title 5."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id798626b0-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1949—Par. (b). Act ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1949-10-28"},"text":"Oct. 28, 1949","children":[],"tail":", substituted “Classification Act of 1949” for “Classification Act of 1923”."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"id798626b1-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"repeals","id":"id798626b2-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Repeals","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1949-10-28/ch782"},"text":"Act Oct. 28, 1949, ch. 782","children":[],"tail":", cited as a credit to this section, was repealed (subject to a savings clause) by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/89/554"},"text":"Pub. L. 89–554","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1966-09-06"},"text":"Sept. 6, 1966","children":[],"tail":", § 8, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/80/632"},"text":"80 Stat. 632","children":[],"tail":", 655."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"transferOfFunctions","id":"id798626b3-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Transfer of Functions","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Secretary of Commerce substituted for Secretary of the Interior in view of transfer of functions to Secretary of Commerce from Secretary of the Interior by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/93/193/s2"},"text":"section 2 of Pub. L. 93–193","children":[],"tail":". See Transfer of Functions note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t15/s1544"},"text":"section 1544 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
